cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper discusses two popular methods for learning vector representations of words, which are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the effectiveness and efficiency of these methods, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the cost functions of these methods, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
